Thank you SAG members! 
First, I am truly excited for the best ensemble nomination, which has made all of our team‚Äôs time spent together on Squid Game even more valuable. 
Working on this series, and acting for the first time, I thought about how creating something ‚Äútogether,‚Äù and ‚Äúas an ensemble‚Äù just might be the true value of our society. 
I feel empowered to be reminded of how ‚Äútogether‚Äù is more precious than a solo achievement. I am truly grateful! I‚Äôm also reminded of our Best Stunt Team, being nominated for the best stunt ensemble nomination. I send all the love and thanks to the best stunt team ever who made sure all of us were safe on the set.Lastly, I was truly taken by surprise that I was nominated. Shall I compare thee to a summer‚Äôs day?
Thou art more lovely and more temperate.
Rough winds do shake the darling buds of May,
And summer‚Äôs lease hath all too short a date.
Sometime too hot the eye of heaven shines,
And often is his gold complexion dimmed;
And every fair from fair sometime declines,
By chance, or nature‚Äôs changing course, untrimmed;
But thy eternal summer shall not fade,
Nor lose possession of that fair thou ow‚Äôst,
Nor shall death brag thou wand'rest in his shade,
When in eternal lines to Time thou grow'st.
 So long as men can breathe, or eyes can see,
 So long lives this, and this gives life to thee.
